> Not to be confused with rice, orzo is actually a type of pasta. Super speedy, this Super Quick Cheesy Bacon Orzo is ready in less than 15 minutes, proving it's not always time you need for delicious dinners.

Boil a full #kettle{}. Pour it into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Boil the @orzo{180%g}, ~{10%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and drizzle with @oil{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, fry the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} and @sliced mushrooms{120%g}, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Next, stir in the @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @creme fraiche{75%g} and @water for the sauce{100%ml}.

Simmer, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

Stir in the Cheddar, @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}, @sun-dried tomato paste{25%g} and orzo. Toss to coat.

Share the orzo between your #bowls{}.

Top with the @wild rocket{20%g} leaves.

Enjoy!